  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Investigation whether a switch from oral iron to intravenous ferric carboxymaltose can reduce
      dose requirements of erythropoiesis-stimulating agents (ESA) and improve Hb levels and iron
      status in adult patients with non-dialysis-dependent CKD who were on a stable ESA/oral iron
      schedule for 6 months prior to enrolment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
